ould cover six sites for `findSunJVM` simply by creating a new `ResolverConfig`. However, if nameservers are empty, will the invocation still be covered?\n\n**Analyzing resource bundle conditions**\n\nFor the `findWin` resource bundle, I need to invoke `findNT` or `find95`. It seems important for `findSunJVM` to fail or for the servers and search list to be unset. The constructor will only proceed with the OS check if `servers` or `searchlist` is null. If `findSunJVM` returns true, then `servers` will be non-null, but I wonder if the search list can still be empty. This setup could impact how I handle server configurations.\n\n**Exploring resource bundles**\n\nI'm trying to figure out the issue with Windows and resource bundles. Skipping Windows seems like it wouldn't work well, as it could trigger `ResourceBundle.getBundle` in `findWin` through the public API. I wonder if the `SimpleResolver` or `Lookup` has properties that I can search for to help with this. There's definitely something here worth investigating further! I want to ensure I find the best solution.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ee368ff6ff029c80169f4daf1a9cc819cba005a0f496d2396\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9NsJGonYyacQV3UBBVtbrbaTyg3cEsAy1uQcfq7Bb4Q19EP8uta-uWxh6h3QJS2RJkxnLzY39xKUUELoMEYnA_5RghPBjuhkPna1nylzD2z888f2EIy6XzMrBobN7u1PiyMhTZKwd6AIU1M7BD3NUbb9GeorQVjvy5NQUfCrNqgHhkS4i3GbQPeDoh-_7La5EoTl7XFPTQc57pOZLg4EafQ3FCDjVAgjmi4Dtz8FumDVg28WNumySHbbssa3YJnQSVL9C5x3hyP0Gh1BRHShUPVGds2atFtmw6B3aWeVjD6AVEG7PWqyAIwHXFbXmHfXLzAEq9-EitZ8CepP2VEYVCoYwqczdxMvlzYeaWFz5S7m3iA8ilbnkdG1OgWjTB9UjXZsIj24-96qKn7-R6E2schuQ_yqkSiGoWEm2M_kq2soMAvdUHlkRr2P3SZdePOAPHnE3HgmRfw7gR1QQR8MbYIThUvdao3-XZ8Ofye6r0M4o9TB0ro9Sh1wpRB6NJZohB88Tjl2E0IIBwCIKhsSTTd1cqC84UWQ8JM36HpkMvHNHvWwJWMUKezMS19SQQ_iRTCiOmVIrLtWjBLFCA80k6JG0__HUE1RS8jLroEZ8SXBhL324qlmV5S0sKBQMDVtSwAM7H2ZEk_d28XMH4ArXHwtG5nzFDrbEJ_7dQwPtF6fEAmWPxi1UH7iVD6z77ohDwDlfTEhJXup3BPu6hZq7PLOoVmQhl5vpumXKLGbYFRhdS-PxElSv8vN18xSjIqpHuWCaM